<plot>Award-winning poet Elizabeth Zetlin walks the limestone barrens of Canada and Ireland. Asking 'what we call holy,' she combines poetry, image and song to create a lyrical meditation on survival and loss. David Suzuki's belief 'the way we see the world shapes the way we treat it' becomes an anthem.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?336925</url></doc>
